title: ICE when pushed to branch of crate in dependencies, `cargo update`, `trunk serve`.

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
<!--
Thank you for finding an Internal Compiler Error! 🧊  If possible, try to provide
a minimal verifiable example. You can read "Rust Bug Minimization Patterns" for
how to create smaller examples.
http://blog.pnkfx.org/blog/2019/11/18/rust-bug-minimization-patterns/
-->

I have a crate in Cargo.toml and it pulls from dev branch on github. I pushed to dev branch on that crate, after that I ran `cargo update` and it updated it, after that I ran `trunk serve` (I'm writing web application) and this happened. I would try to create minimal verifiable example later.

Sequence of my actions:
Work with "https://github.com/AVO-cado-team/ramemu.git" in "https://github.com/Ddystopia/ram-webgui/tree/ICE"
Change code in "https://github.com/AVO-cado-team/ramemu.git" (I just added one line of code, implementing some trait)
Push to dev branch of "https://github.com/AVO-cado-team/ramemu.git"
In "https://github.com/Ddystopia/ram-webgui/tree/ICE":
Stop `trunk serve`, it did not update "https://github.com/AVO-cado-team/ramemu.git".
Run `cargo update`
Run `trunk serve`
ICE

From Cargo.toml
```toml
[dependencies.ramemu]
git = "https://github.com/AVO-cado-team/ramemu.git"
branch = "dev"
features = ["wasm"]
```

That is code:
[https://github.com/Ddystopia/ram-webgui/tree/ICE](https://github.com/Ddystopia/ram-webgui/tree/ICE)
Crate, after pushing to which it happened: https://github.com/AVO-cado-team/ramemu/tree/dev

Crate in dependencies was pushed from `9423019` to `bc4f4c3`

Thank you for reading this issue, I would love to provide any additional information.

### Meta
